Given an integer x, return true if x is a 
palindrome
, and false otherwise.

 

Example 1:

Input: x = 121
Output: true
Explanation: 121 reads as 121 from left to right and from right to left.

answer:
class Solution {
    public boolean isPalindrome(int x) {
        if (x < 0 || (x > 0 && x % 10 == 0)) {
            return false;
        }
        int y = 0;
        for (; y < x; x /= 10) {
            y = y * 10 + x % 10;
        }
        return x == y || x == y / 10;
    }
}
